1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,876
(Previously) Your family still doesn't know
about the thick-browed guy?

2
00:00:01,900 --> 00:00:04,695
Yeah. I was going to tell them,
but I didn't get the chance.

3
00:00:04,713 --> 00:00:07,803
You just have to transform me into a pilot.

4
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:08,972
Hello.

5
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:10,505
I came straight here as soon as I landed.

6
00:00:10,529 --> 00:00:11,588
I'm talking about you and Kanit.

7
00:00:11,612 --> 00:00:13,009
Are you serious about him?

8
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:14,449
I've loved you from the moment we met.

9
00:00:14,461 --> 00:00:16,341
I want to fly with you
for the rest of my life.

10
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:21,560
Help!

11
00:00:23,495 --> 00:00:24,495
Ma'am.

12
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:27,625
If you're going to keep seeing each other,
you better improve your life.

13
00:00:27,649 --> 00:00:30,381
Make yourself worthy of my son.

14
00:00:30,412 --> 00:00:33,230
If you can't do that, then break up.

15
00:00:33,273 --> 00:00:34,273
Don't worry.

16
00:00:34,610 --> 00:00:35,489
I'm not giving up.

17
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:36,923
I'll prove to your dad

18
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:38,920
that I'm the best for you.

19
00:00:58,978 --> 00:01:01,624
How come you've been hanging out with me
so much lately?

20
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:05,975
Don't people who are dating
usually ditch their friends?

21
00:01:07,270 --> 00:01:08,707
Well, he's busy.

22
00:01:08,726 --> 00:01:10,646
He's working multiple
shifts and jobs right now.

23
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:13,396
So our schedules don't really align.

24
00:01:13,427 --> 00:01:16,153
I can hear the hurt in your voice.

25
00:01:16,178 --> 00:01:20,129
It's giving, "What's the point of having
a partner if we never see each other?"

26
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:21,360
Don't you agree?

27
00:01:22,246 --> 00:01:24,240
I'm trying to understand him though.

28
00:01:25,570 --> 00:01:29,784
You need to bring back
the spark in your relationship.

29
00:01:29,827 --> 00:01:33,335
Turn the time you get
to spend together into

30
00:01:33,353 --> 00:01:34,353
something hot!

31
00:01:35,140 --> 00:01:36,140
How?

32
00:01:39,926 --> 00:01:41,224
Yoga in bed.

33
00:01:44,049 --> 00:01:44,547
Please.

34
00:01:44,790 --> 00:01:45,760
When would we even do that?

35
00:01:45,790 --> 00:01:48,178
The second he gets home,
he's fast asleep from exhaustion.

36
00:01:48,590 --> 00:01:51,446
You can't let that go on.

37
00:01:51,464 --> 00:01:52,984
Your relationship will get worse.

38
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:57,575
I think you have to do something
to make your love life sweeter.

39
00:01:57,980 --> 00:01:59,261
Like sweet as sugar.

40
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:00,381
Sweet as sugar?

41
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:02,283
Try to think outside the box.

42
00:02:02,332 --> 00:02:04,806
Maybe you can give him a surprise.

43
00:02:04,836 --> 00:02:08,104
Who knows? He might want to
leave the bodies and hurry home to you.

44
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:17,292
It's on now.

45
00:02:17,316 --> 00:02:18,436
Okay. All done.

46
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:19,840
Here's your pay.

47
00:02:49,130 --> 00:02:49,803
Enjoy.

48
00:02:49,827 --> 00:02:50,330
Thank you.

49
00:02:50,363 --> 00:02:51,126
I'll take it from here, Boss.

50
00:02:51,150 --> 00:02:52,800
Thank you, Boss.

51
00:02:53,140 --> 00:02:53,956
So generous.

52
00:02:53,987 --> 00:02:55,618
Come on. I'll hand these out.

53
00:02:55,667 --> 00:02:56,667
Oh.

54
00:02:56,820 --> 00:02:57,820
Hey, To.

55
00:02:57,990 --> 00:03:02,110
When can I work for your company,
Everything Can or something like that?

56
00:03:02,135 --> 00:03:04,175
I'll let you know
when there's a job that suits you.

57
00:03:05,050 --> 00:03:08,510
But let me warn you,
you won't really get any rest.

58
00:03:08,553 --> 00:03:10,683
If you don't need money that badly,
don't do it.

59
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:13,378
Don't work too hard without taking a break.

60
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:15,476
We don't want to pick up your dead body.

61
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:17,100
Shut up. Give the shrimp back.

62
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,080
No.

63
00:03:18,116 --> 00:03:19,095
She's right.

64
00:03:19,138 --> 00:03:22,030
But if you die, call us
the first day you die, okay?

65
00:03:22,055 --> 00:03:23,791
If you leave it a couple days, your body
will bloat and I won't remember you.

66
00:03:23,815 --> 00:03:24,843
Your bloated body

67
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:32,030
could have pus and yellowish fluid
oozing out of your eyes.

68
00:03:32,049 --> 00:03:33,643
You know who'd die before me?

69
00:03:33,686 --> 00:03:34,686
Who?

70
00:03:34,830 --> 00:03:35,830
It's you, jerk!

71
00:03:36,380 --> 00:03:37,360
Come on, Beer.

72
00:03:37,403 --> 00:03:39,649
You said that so vividly
I can't eat anymore.

73
00:03:39,667 --> 00:03:40,667
Sorry.

74
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:43,710
By the way, have you found an admin
to handle your bookings?

75
00:03:43,741 --> 00:03:44,741
Not yet.

76
00:03:44,890 --> 00:03:47,187
My schedule is clashing so much right now.

77
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:48,966
Where can I find one?

78
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,276
Hand out the shrimp.

79
00:03:50,295 --> 00:03:50,910
Ja-O.

80
00:03:51,310 --> 00:03:52,310
- Thank you.
- Can I help?

81
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:54,560
Oh, hey, Por.

82
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:56,420
It's fine.

83
00:03:56,670 --> 00:03:58,098
You're busy enough
with the foundation's accounting work.

84
00:03:58,116 --> 00:03:58,695
I don't want to trouble you.

85
00:03:58,744 --> 00:03:59,920
I can help.

86
00:03:59,956 --> 00:04:01,316
It's not that demanding.

87
00:04:01,932 --> 00:04:03,252
Besides, I don't want you to die.

88
00:04:05,510 --> 00:04:06,867
Are you sure you want to help?

89
00:04:06,898 --> 00:04:07,261
Mm.

90
00:04:07,285 --> 00:04:08,473
The pay won't be much.

91
00:04:08,541 --> 00:04:10,264
Just ask, and I'll do it for free.

92
00:04:10,301 --> 00:04:10,996
Don't worry.

93
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,560
Are you serious?

94
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,975
Join us for this meal then.

95
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,030
Come on, eat with us.

96
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:20,215
Are you serious?

97
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:21,495
Yeah.

98
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:24,240
Why do you get two,
but we only get one each?

99
00:04:24,516 --> 00:04:25,636
I tried it for you.

100
00:04:25,655 --> 00:04:26,067
Please!

101
00:04:26,086 --> 00:04:27,341
Just in case it's poisoned.

102
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:25,300
"A Dog and A Plane"
(Episode 8)

103
00:05:31,450 --> 00:05:32,127
It's almost 9 p.m.

104
00:05:32,146 --> 00:05:33,530
Please, no more cases right now.

105
00:05:33,555 --> 00:05:34,681
I want to take a nap.

106
00:05:39,020 --> 00:05:40,020
Hey, To.

107
00:05:41,370 --> 00:05:42,312
Go ahead and sleep.

108
00:05:42,355 --> 00:05:44,386
If anyone bothers you, just let me know.

109
00:05:44,416 --> 00:05:45,420
I'll deal with them.

110
00:05:46,460 --> 00:05:47,460
Thanks.

111
00:05:49,190 --> 00:05:50,570
Hey, To.

112
00:05:50,595 --> 00:05:51,595
To.

113
00:05:51,740 --> 00:05:53,063
What is it now?

114
00:05:53,087 --> 00:05:55,167
Ja-O bothered you while you were sleeping,
didn't he?

115
00:05:55,690 --> 00:05:56,343
Keep sleeping.

116
00:05:56,367 --> 00:05:57,481
I'll deal with him.

117
00:05:57,506 --> 00:05:58,829
I'll keep a lookout, bro.

118
00:05:58,847 --> 00:06:01,063
Yeah, don't bother me now. Let me sleep.

119
00:06:06,570 --> 00:06:07,570
Hey, To.

120
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:09,420
What?

121
00:06:09,450 --> 00:06:11,296
Beer bothered you just now, right?

122
00:06:11,910 --> 00:06:13,198
He's terrible, isn't he?

123
00:06:13,210 --> 00:06:15,190
You're the one bothering him.

124
00:06:15,216 --> 00:06:17,321
Can't you see I'm
keeping a lookout for him?

125
00:06:17,352 --> 00:06:18,884
I'm not bothering him.

126
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:19,580
You were doing this.

127
00:06:19,604 --> 00:06:20,774
You put his hand on him like this,

128
00:06:20,798 --> 00:06:22,066
and you were shaking him, weren't you?

129
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,370
I wasn't shaking him.

130
00:06:23,407 --> 00:06:24,127
You were.

131
00:06:24,146 --> 00:06:24,706
Exactly like this.

132
00:06:24,730 --> 00:06:25,678
Idiots!

133
00:06:25,715 --> 00:06:27,820
Don't make me scold both of you.

134
00:06:27,856 --> 00:06:29,543
Quiet. I'm trying to sleep.

135
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,040
Come on!

136
00:06:41,070 --> 00:06:42,127
Hey, To.

137
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:43,930
There's something urgent.

138
00:06:43,967 --> 00:06:45,370
What the hell is urgent now?

139
00:06:46,287 --> 00:06:46,995
To,

140
00:06:47,020 --> 00:06:48,263
you need to wake up and see this.

141
00:06:48,287 --> 00:06:49,893
This is real. I'm not pranking you.

142
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,878
Ugh! What is it now?

143
00:07:01,570 --> 00:07:03,130
I don't think you're getting any sleep.

144
00:07:11,450 --> 00:07:13,986
Would you like some dessert, sir?

145
00:07:15,980 --> 00:07:17,420
It definitely is ready to be served.

146
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:22,115
But I forgot to bring a spoon and fork.

147
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:25,013
If you'd like to have it,

148
00:07:25,438 --> 00:07:26,540
please use your mouth, sir.

149
00:07:30,540 --> 00:07:32,300
Your passenger smells really bad right now.

150
00:07:32,903 --> 00:07:34,943
Let me go take a shower first,
Mr. Flight Attendant.

151
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,120
I don't mind.

152
00:07:39,110 --> 00:07:40,190
You don't smell bad at all.

153
00:07:41,550 --> 00:07:42,681
You smell really nice.

154
00:07:43,890 --> 00:07:44,890
I'll start eating then.

155
00:08:03,710 --> 00:08:04,710
How is it?

156
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:06,270
Sweet?

157
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:08,900
Hey.

158
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:12,220
Hey.

159
00:08:34,460 --> 00:08:35,623
You're up.

160
00:08:37,140 --> 00:08:38,570
I made you breakfast.

161
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:41,469
Why didn't you wake me up last night?

162
00:08:41,806 --> 00:08:44,390
You literally passed out.
How could I wake you up?

163
00:08:46,610 --> 00:08:48,907
I have no idea when I passed out.

164
00:08:48,926 --> 00:08:50,040
I'm sorry.

165
00:08:50,083 --> 00:08:50,667
Mm.

166
00:08:51,090 --> 00:08:52,575
I really didn't realize it.

167
00:08:52,606 --> 00:08:53,978
Yeah, stop talking.

168
00:08:55,620 --> 00:08:56,620
Are you sulking?

169
00:08:56,650 --> 00:08:57,650
No.

170
00:08:58,620 --> 00:08:59,978
Come on, are you sulking?

171
00:09:00,003 --> 00:09:00,513
No.

172
00:09:00,930 --> 00:09:02,212
You're definitely sulking.

173
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,169
I'm awake now.

174
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:10,870
Let me finish my dessert.

175
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,520
Stop.

176
00:09:12,544 --> 00:09:13,276
Whoa.

177
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:14,772
You still have whipped cream on your lips.

178
00:09:14,796 --> 00:09:15,695
Let me finish it.

179
00:09:15,732 --> 00:09:16,732
It's messy.

180
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:17,406
No.

181
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:18,895
I have to go to work.

182
00:09:18,926 --> 00:09:20,710
Come on, why?

183
00:09:20,747 --> 00:09:21,756
Don't go.

184
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:23,720
I have to go now before traffic gets bad.

185
00:09:23,744 --> 00:09:24,729
Eat your breakfast.

186
00:09:24,766 --> 00:09:25,769
What?

187
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:30,064
You said you weren't sulking.

188
00:09:30,101 --> 00:09:31,101
I'm not.

189
00:09:33,350 --> 00:09:34,827
You're definitely sulking.

190
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,403
I was exhausted last night.

191
00:09:40,433 --> 00:09:41,621
I really was.

192
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:52,870
Next time, I won't leave a single bite.

193
00:10:24,870 --> 00:10:25,596
Here you go.

194
00:10:25,615 --> 00:10:26,615
Thank you.

195
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,200
Hey.

196
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:37,550
What brings you here?

197
00:10:38,290 --> 00:10:39,400
Maybe I took a bus.

198
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,240
Are you trying to get on my nerves?

199
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:44,243
I told you. I'm joining the race.

200
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,500
Hey.

201
00:10:48,070 --> 00:10:49,070
What about your headband?

202
00:11:02,310 --> 00:11:03,310
Here.

203
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:06,236
My hands are greasy.

204
00:11:07,170 --> 00:11:08,532
That's fine.

205
00:11:08,820 --> 00:11:09,836
Let me put it on you.

206
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:12,520
No need.

207
00:11:12,563 --> 00:11:13,824
My hair will be a mess.

208
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:15,246
No, it won't.

209
00:11:15,283 --> 00:11:16,283
Stay still.

210
00:11:16,490 --> 00:11:17,490
Don't be stubborn.

211
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:18,880
You don't have to.

212
00:11:19,130 --> 00:11:21,130
Once I'm done applying this,
I'll put it on myself.

213
00:11:21,830 --> 00:11:23,129
I said I'd do it for you.

214
00:11:23,850 --> 00:11:25,061
I'll do it myself.

215
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:30,730
Will you stay still now?

216
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:35,720
Hmm?

217
00:11:35,930 --> 00:11:36,930
Will you?

218
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:41,898
I'm already still.

219
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,890
You take care of so many passengers.

220
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:10,280
Let me take care of you.

221
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:19,812
Please gather at the starting point
in 10 minutes.

222
00:12:19,855 --> 00:12:21,006
We're about to start.

223
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:23,610
Hey.

224
00:12:23,650 --> 00:12:24,981
Are you sure you're going to run?

225
00:12:25,350 --> 00:12:27,670
Let me warn you.
This isn't just any typical running event.

226
00:12:28,270 --> 00:12:29,950
I didn't come to just run casually either.

227
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:32,181
I'm serious about everything.

228
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:35,030
Whether it's this race

229
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:38,030
or pursuing you.

230
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:40,500
Up to you then.

231
00:12:45,073 --> 00:12:46,600
Ready?

232
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,852
Three. Two. One.

233
00:12:48,895 --> 00:12:49,895
Go!

234
00:13:23,966 --> 00:13:25,960
Today's obstacles were a walk in the park.

235
00:13:25,996 --> 00:13:27,449
Can I get something more challenging
next time?

236
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:29,049
Stop bragging.

237
00:13:29,067 --> 00:13:31,467
I saw you panting while running.

238
00:13:31,492 --> 00:13:33,460
I was panting because
you couldn't catch up.

239
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:37,400
I was waiting for you
so we could cross the finish line together.

240
00:13:44,220 --> 00:13:45,220
You know what?

241
00:13:45,590 --> 00:13:48,833
I've never gotten a
medal in my entire life.

242
00:13:49,210 --> 00:13:50,850
I've never won anything like this before.

243
00:13:53,970 --> 00:13:55,424
You won today.

244
00:13:56,220 --> 00:13:57,406
You won my heart too.

245
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:05,467
Won't you say something?

246
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,123
What do you want me to say?

247
00:14:08,020 --> 00:14:09,652
You flirted with me so hard.

248
00:14:10,340 --> 00:14:11,818
I'm blushing.

249
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:20,480
Ki.

250
00:14:23,190 --> 00:14:24,190
Ki?

251
00:14:28,690 --> 00:14:29,930
Did you finish taking a shower?

252
00:14:30,710 --> 00:14:31,710
No.

253
00:14:39,570 --> 00:14:41,424
But I want to see you blush.

254
00:14:45,610 --> 00:14:47,941
You know what the
hardest obstacle was today?

255
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:51,300
This.

256
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:54,612
How am I supposed to
clear this obstacle, huh?

257
00:14:55,990 --> 00:14:58,433
You already cleared it
the day you saved me at the airport.

258
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:05,775
You know what? The first day
I saw your face again made me realize

259
00:15:07,049 --> 00:15:08,689
a first love is hard to get over after all.

260
00:15:17,380 --> 00:15:18,415
Then…

261
00:15:20,270 --> 00:15:25,393
let me give you another goal medal today.

262
00:16:09,550 --> 00:16:10,550
Oh!

263
00:16:11,230 --> 00:16:12,532
Why are you staring at my face?

264
00:16:13,350 --> 00:16:14,636
I'm not staring.

265
00:16:14,660 --> 00:16:15,566
I'm listening to you snore.

266
00:16:15,584 --> 00:16:16,666
It's as loud as an earthquake.

267
00:16:16,690 --> 00:16:17,690
You're exaggerating.

268
00:16:18,410 --> 00:16:20,236
I don't usually snore this loud.

269
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:21,280
I'm just tired.

270
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:23,147
Then why don't you take a break?

271
00:16:23,172 --> 00:16:24,200
Live your life.

272
00:16:25,810 --> 00:16:27,664
I have to hit my goal.

273
00:16:30,270 --> 00:16:32,366
Your goal is to marry
your boyfriend, right?

274
00:16:35,990 --> 00:16:36,990
Oh.

275
00:16:37,220 --> 00:16:38,353
Beer and the others were talking about it.

276
00:16:38,372 --> 00:16:39,372
I overheard.

277
00:16:40,030 --> 00:16:41,387
I'm not there yet.

278
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:43,615
It's just a plan for now.

279
00:16:48,990 --> 00:16:50,840
A job came in,

280
00:16:50,876 --> 00:16:52,292
but seeing how exhausted you are…

281
00:16:52,329 --> 00:16:52,981
Let me turn it down.

282
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,000
What? No!

283
00:16:54,390 --> 00:16:55,390
What kind of job?

284
00:16:56,650 --> 00:16:58,747
"I can't" isn't in Toto's vocabulary.

285
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:05,504
Come on.

286
00:17:05,523 --> 00:17:06,550
Bring on the work.

287
00:17:06,569 --> 00:17:07,633
Pile it on now.

288
00:17:07,664 --> 00:17:08,396
I love a heavy workload.

289
00:17:08,409 --> 00:17:09,726
I love working, not sleeping.

290
00:17:09,756 --> 00:17:11,720
Keep the work coming. I love my job.

291
00:17:12,080 --> 00:17:13,553
Come on. What's the job?

292
00:17:13,584 --> 00:17:15,301
It's cleaning a swimming pool.

293
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,612
A pretty big one.

294
00:17:16,636 --> 00:17:17,843
The tip should be hefty.

295
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:18,360
Send me the location.

296
00:17:18,384 --> 00:17:19,384
What are you waiting for?

297
00:17:20,420 --> 00:17:21,209
I need to poop real quick.

298
00:17:21,233 --> 00:17:22,233
I'll be right back.

299
00:17:29,184 --> 00:17:31,180
Yeah, I'm at their house.

300
00:17:31,890 --> 00:17:33,535
When I'm done, I get paid in cash, right?

301
00:17:34,330 --> 00:17:35,615
Thanks a lot, Por,

302
00:17:36,290 --> 00:17:37,627
for listening to my rant.

303
00:17:42,370 --> 00:17:43,424
Help me!

304
00:17:45,310 --> 00:17:46,372
Help me!

305
00:17:46,860 --> 00:17:47,498
Help!

306
00:17:47,510 --> 00:17:48,510
Hey, you!

307
00:17:48,606 --> 00:17:50,600
Uh… you okay?

308
00:17:51,140 --> 00:17:51,818
What's wrong?

309
00:17:51,836 --> 00:17:53,252
Did you fall down the stairs?

310
00:17:53,930 --> 00:17:55,172
Alright, what should I do?

311
00:17:55,190 --> 00:17:56,883
Are you hurt? Hurt where?

312
00:17:56,901 --> 00:17:58,880
Don't worry. You won't die.

313
00:17:59,090 --> 00:18:00,200
It's far from your heart.

314
00:18:00,230 --> 00:18:01,230
I can speak Thai.

315
00:18:01,590 --> 00:18:01,972
Huh?

316
00:18:02,009 --> 00:18:03,061
I can speak Thai.

317
00:18:03,104 --> 00:18:04,104
Oh, okay.

318
00:18:04,510 --> 00:18:05,510
Okay. Does it hurt?

319
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:06,446
Yes.

320
00:18:06,470 --> 00:18:08,440
Where does it hurt?

321
00:18:08,470 --> 00:18:09,301
Here or where?

322
00:18:09,326 --> 00:18:09,910
Here.

323
00:18:09,935 --> 00:18:10,286
Here?

324
00:18:10,310 --> 00:18:10,710
Yeah.

325
00:18:10,747 --> 00:18:11,633
Okay.

326
00:18:11,670 --> 00:18:13,630
You twisted your ankle.

327
00:18:13,780 --> 00:18:14,692
I'll help you.

328
00:18:14,710 --> 00:18:15,233
Okay.

329
00:18:15,270 --> 00:18:16,270
Stand up.

330
00:18:18,610 --> 00:18:19,092
Okay.

331
00:18:19,110 --> 00:18:20,169
Walk slowly.

332
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:22,132
What's going on, Steve?

333
00:18:39,460 --> 00:18:40,460
Toto.

334
00:18:42,190 --> 00:18:44,273
This is for cleaning the pool.

335
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:59,043
And this is extra for you.

336
00:19:02,170 --> 00:19:03,170
It's fine.

337
00:19:03,970 --> 00:19:05,535
I'll only take the fee we agreed on.

338
00:19:07,270 --> 00:19:09,252
How are you doing?

339
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:10,640
How's Tonlew?

340
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:15,140
She's fine.

341
00:19:15,910 --> 00:19:16,910
Don't worry.

342
00:19:18,290 --> 00:19:20,090
She's my only sister.
I can take care of her.

343
00:19:21,460 --> 00:19:24,384
I heard you sent her to a good school.

344
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,744
Keep this for her tuition.

345
00:19:31,584 --> 00:19:33,580
I only take money I work for.

346
00:19:35,360 --> 00:19:37,012
I won't take anything that's not mine.

347
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:44,673
I'll drop by your house sometime then.

348
00:19:44,987 --> 00:19:45,987
There's no need.

349
00:19:51,060 --> 00:19:54,089
Does your foreign husband even know
you have kids?

350
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,600
It's alright. I'm not going to tell him.

351
00:19:59,650 --> 00:20:01,141
I'm sure you'll get by just fine.

352
00:20:03,890 --> 00:20:06,171
My sister and I can manage
without relying on an outsider.

353
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:15,369
Your pool is clean now.

354
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:42,083
Hey.

355
00:20:42,350 --> 00:20:44,532
You should be resting,

356
00:20:44,556 --> 00:20:46,196
but here you are on a date with me again.

357
00:20:46,670 --> 00:20:47,836
It's just yawning.

358
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:50,219
Whether I get a lot
of sleep or not, I yawn.

359
00:20:50,243 --> 00:20:51,243
It's irrelevant.

360
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:55,732
I'd rather be on a date with you.

361
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:58,735
Don't worry about me.

362
00:20:59,350 --> 00:21:01,424
I can manage my time. It's chill.

363
00:21:02,930 --> 00:21:04,316
And I want to apologize

364
00:21:06,310 --> 00:21:08,350
for not finishing the whipped cream
the other night.

365
00:21:09,990 --> 00:21:12,163
Stop it. I've already washed it all off.

366
00:21:14,160 --> 00:21:15,160
Come on.

367
00:21:15,330 --> 00:21:16,330
I'm wide awake.

368
00:21:17,090 --> 00:21:18,550
I'm ready to be your guide now.

369
00:21:20,532 --> 00:21:21,941
Look, Mr. Kanit.

370
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:23,892
This lizard is called a Bearded Dragon.

371
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:26,316
And this is Gilo-what?

372
00:21:26,341 --> 00:21:26,846
Gila!

373
00:21:26,864 --> 00:21:28,280
Gila monster.

374
00:21:28,329 --> 00:21:29,006
Look.

375
00:21:29,043 --> 00:21:30,630
You brought me on a date to a zoo?

376
00:21:30,649 --> 00:21:31,929
What kind of man are you?

377
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:36,673
How many men in your life
would bring you to see dwarf crocodiles?

378
00:21:37,460 --> 00:21:38,649
I'm limited edition.

379
00:21:39,770 --> 00:21:42,803
By the way, what are you going to do
about your mom?

380
00:21:46,120 --> 00:21:48,938
She's been calling,
but I haven't picked up.

381
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:53,750
She also texted me
that she wanted to see Tonlew.

382
00:21:55,030 --> 00:21:56,046
But I don't want them to see each other.

383
00:21:56,070 --> 00:21:59,332
Well, have you asked your sister
if she wants to see her mom?

384
00:21:59,498 --> 00:22:01,018
Why not let her make her own decision?

385
00:22:02,076 --> 00:22:04,070
I know what my sister wants.

386
00:22:04,810 --> 00:22:06,144
I've raised her!

387
00:22:07,540 --> 00:22:08,846
Why did you raise your voice?

388
00:22:09,220 --> 00:22:11,981
Careful, the crocodiles might freak out
and jump up to bite your neck.

389
00:22:12,650 --> 00:22:13,650
Come this way.

390
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:15,240
I'm sorry.

391
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:22,735
Why are we sitting down?

392
00:22:23,060 --> 00:22:25,332
I haven't gotten a look
at the dwarf crocodiles yet.

393
00:22:26,107 --> 00:22:26,784
Hey,

394
00:22:26,809 --> 00:22:28,187
let the crocodiles go to sleep.

395
00:22:28,206 --> 00:22:29,627
You should wake up.

396
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:30,960
I'm already up.

397
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:33,240
Here.

398
00:22:34,130 --> 00:22:35,130
Look.

399
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:36,593
Eat this.

400
00:22:36,624 --> 00:22:37,836
Chewing it will keep you awake.

401
00:22:37,855 --> 00:22:38,855
Nom.

402
00:22:43,290 --> 00:22:44,290
Whoa.

403
00:22:45,535 --> 00:22:49,584
You know, since the day you made me
try this, I haven't stopped eating it.

404
00:22:54,260 --> 00:22:56,790
Thank you so much
for still putting up with me,

405
00:22:58,660 --> 00:23:02,187
even though I passed out on you
that night while you were being so sexy.

406
00:23:04,089 --> 00:23:05,606
Not to mention, I accidentally
snapped at you today.

407
00:23:05,630 --> 00:23:09,141
It's alright. I don't hold it against you
when your blood sugar drops.

408
00:23:09,570 --> 00:23:12,292
I promise that from now on,

409
00:23:13,140 --> 00:23:14,636
I'll be a good boyfriend

410
00:23:15,330 --> 00:23:16,747
who has time for you.

411
00:23:18,850 --> 00:23:21,516
If I can't do it, I will…

412
00:23:24,130 --> 00:23:27,320
I'll feed myself to the dwarf crocodiles.

413
00:23:28,390 --> 00:23:30,403
Oh, those babies are
getting ready to be fed.

414
00:23:30,730 --> 00:23:32,090
They'll definitely get to eat you.

415
00:23:32,590 --> 00:23:35,153
Meanwhile, you should eat this.

416
00:23:57,276 --> 00:23:57,806
Hey!

417
00:23:58,200 --> 00:23:59,200
Easy, kid!

418
00:24:02,230 --> 00:24:03,307
Look, you're matching.

419
00:24:03,338 --> 00:24:04,606
You both have dark circles.

420
00:24:05,110 --> 00:24:06,110
Hey.

421
00:24:06,649 --> 00:24:07,418
This one looks like you.

422
00:24:07,455 --> 00:24:09,406
♪ With you and me together ♪

423
00:24:09,443 --> 00:24:12,409
♪ Every day, just like this ♪

424
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:14,747
♪ Through both the
good and stormy weather ♪

425
00:24:14,778 --> 00:24:18,181
♪ Love needs no reason for this ♪

426
00:24:18,212 --> 00:24:20,255
♪ It can't be wrong ♪

427
00:24:20,292 --> 00:24:23,018
♪ To not care what people say ♪

428
00:24:23,049 --> 00:24:25,775
♪ When it comes to me and you ♪

429
00:24:25,818 --> 00:24:30,169
♪ We are the reason that stays ♪

430
00:24:38,787 --> 00:24:39,787
Hey, Ki.

431
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:41,360
What are we doing here?

432
00:24:41,753 --> 00:24:42,960
To repeat a school year?

433
00:24:44,190 --> 00:24:45,190
Can we?

434
00:24:45,780 --> 00:24:48,036
You can be the Grade 10 kid
and I'll be your Grade 12 senior again.

435
00:24:48,055 --> 00:24:50,584
But this time, you don't have to
crush on me in secret.

436
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:51,920
Because…

437
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:53,464
you're my boyfriend now.

438
00:24:54,050 --> 00:24:56,233
Let's make new memories together.

439
00:24:56,810 --> 00:24:57,858
Let's vibe.

440
00:24:58,590 --> 00:25:01,593
♪ I feel 14 again ♪

441
00:25:23,390 --> 00:25:23,932
Hmm?

442
00:25:24,380 --> 00:25:28,104
I never thought that one day,
I'd get to eat with Ki,

443
00:25:28,980 --> 00:25:30,369
the senior I used to swoon over.

444
00:25:34,230 --> 00:25:35,347
Wanna swoon even more?

445
00:25:36,190 --> 00:25:37,190
What?

446
00:25:41,020 --> 00:25:43,803
Everyone, listen here!

447
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:47,101
This is Veha from Grade 10, Class 5.

448
00:25:47,550 --> 00:25:49,809
He's dating Ki from Grade 12, Class 2.

449
00:25:50,190 --> 00:25:51,981
Don't anyone dare get close to him.

450
00:25:56,978 --> 00:25:57,980
Sit down!

451
00:26:03,980 --> 00:26:05,193
Sit down!

452
00:26:05,790 --> 00:26:06,790
Hey, Ki!

453
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:08,147
What are you doing?

454
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,625
You're freaking the kids out.

455
00:26:09,649 --> 00:26:10,676
They think you're crazy.

456
00:26:14,184 --> 00:26:15,858
Hey, Tua. I'm sorry.

457
00:26:15,890 --> 00:26:17,956
I wanted to impress my boyfriend.

458
00:26:18,940 --> 00:26:19,864
This is Veha.

459
00:26:19,883 --> 00:26:20,947
You know him, right?

460
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:23,500
Of course.

461
00:26:24,030 --> 00:26:25,809
He's been your fan since high school.

462
00:26:26,300 --> 00:26:27,300
By the way, Akki,

463
00:26:27,790 --> 00:26:29,495
the school is looking for a P.E. teacher.

464
00:26:29,520 --> 00:26:30,520
Are you interested?

465
00:26:31,370 --> 00:26:32,730
You can be the football coach too.

466
00:26:33,450 --> 00:26:35,015
If you teach the kids

467
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:36,160
and coach our football team,

468
00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:38,344
we'll definitely win.

469
00:26:40,630 --> 00:26:42,892
I haven't played football in a long time.

470
00:26:43,430 --> 00:26:44,818
You should find someone else.

471
00:26:46,390 --> 00:26:47,870
It'd be a shame to waste your talent.

472
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:51,840
Alright, never mind.

473
00:26:51,876 --> 00:26:52,876
I should get going.

474
00:26:53,490 --> 00:26:57,003
Oh, and don't shout again
or I'll call security on you.

475
00:26:57,390 --> 00:26:57,895
Yeah.

476
00:26:57,913 --> 00:26:58,913
I'm off.

477
00:27:05,230 --> 00:27:06,230
Hey.

478
00:27:07,030 --> 00:27:08,430
Are you sure you're not interested?

479
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,603
I think it's a great opportunity.

480
00:27:11,540 --> 00:27:14,221
No, I prefer working as a rescuer.

481
00:27:14,810 --> 00:27:16,166
I can barely take care of myself.

482
00:27:16,190 --> 00:27:17,550
How am I supposed to teach anyone?

483
00:27:27,050 --> 00:27:28,050
So nice.

484
00:27:29,500 --> 00:27:32,098
Soaking in a tub with you feels amazing.

485
00:27:32,680 --> 00:27:34,480
So much better than
going to a massage parlor.

486
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:37,360
Wait, have you been to that kind of place?

487
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:40,873
Oh, I was a little
naughty before I met you.

488
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:43,298
I used to be a tiger, you know?

489
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:46,098
Hmm… What are you now?

490
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:47,800
Still a tiger,

491
00:27:49,366 --> 00:27:50,763
but I've lost my claws.

492
00:27:51,430 --> 00:27:54,080
Now I'm just a clingy little kitten

493
00:27:54,460 --> 00:27:55,618
that wants to nuzzle

494
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:57,409
and cuddle my owner all day.

495
00:27:58,180 --> 00:27:59,193
Little kitten.

496
00:27:59,218 --> 00:28:00,430
Meow.

497
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:03,298
Ugh!

498
00:28:04,810 --> 00:28:06,024
I'm not answering that.

499
00:28:06,043 --> 00:28:07,366
It's been a long day for me.

500
00:28:07,403 --> 00:28:08,812
Let me get cozy with my boyfriend.

501
00:28:08,849 --> 00:28:10,098
Can you not disturb us?

502
00:28:11,370 --> 00:28:12,603
Let me go back to being a kitten.

503
00:28:12,627 --> 00:28:13,698
Come here, kitten.

504
00:28:13,716 --> 00:28:15,526
Meow, meow.

505
00:28:16,640 --> 00:28:18,295
Meow, meow, meow, meow.

506
00:28:28,020 --> 00:28:29,483
What the hell?

507
00:28:29,520 --> 00:28:31,316
We're trying to have a moment here!

508
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:34,560
You can take the call. I don't mind.

509
00:28:35,260 --> 00:28:36,260
It might be urgent.

510
00:28:39,910 --> 00:28:40,615
What's up, Por?

511
00:28:40,650 --> 00:28:42,492
To, something's wrong with Je Zo.

512
00:28:42,516 --> 00:28:43,340
Come help.

513
00:28:43,384 --> 00:28:45,360
Oh, what's wrong?

514
00:28:46,190 --> 00:28:47,255
How is he doing?

515
00:28:47,286 --> 00:28:48,215
I don't know.

516
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:49,163
We were eating,

517
00:28:49,181 --> 00:28:50,578
and he just collapsed.

518
00:28:50,603 --> 00:28:51,476
Come here quickly.

519
00:28:51,507 --> 00:28:52,153
Okay.

520
00:28:52,190 --> 00:28:53,190
I'm coming right over.

521
00:28:53,990 --> 00:28:56,461
Hey, Por said Je Zo passed out.

522
00:28:56,486 --> 00:28:57,566
Something's wrong with him.

523
00:28:58,520 --> 00:28:59,575
I need to go and help.

524
00:29:00,030 --> 00:29:01,310
Do you want me to come with you?

525
00:29:01,630 --> 00:29:03,409
It's okay. I'll hurry back.

526
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:11,390
Hey, Por.

527
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:13,747
You said Je Zo fainted.

528
00:29:15,130 --> 00:29:16,572
Why are you two drinking?

529
00:29:16,603 --> 00:29:17,913
Well, he's awake now.

530
00:29:17,944 --> 00:29:19,446
He was just exhausted.

531
00:29:19,501 --> 00:29:21,735
I tried to make him go home,
but he wouldn't listen.

532
00:29:21,772 --> 00:29:22,695
He's so stubborn.

533
00:29:22,750 --> 00:29:24,307
Don't scold him.

534
00:29:24,332 --> 00:29:26,196
I'm the one who wanted to drink.

535
00:29:26,610 --> 00:29:28,209
I just needed to vent.

536
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,246
I'm stressed.

537
00:29:32,130 --> 00:29:33,587
And here I thought you were dead.

538
00:29:34,850 --> 00:29:36,024
I'm leaving then.

539
00:29:36,670 --> 00:29:37,372
My boyfriend is waiting.

540
00:29:37,390 --> 00:29:38,504
Hey, wait.

541
00:29:38,529 --> 00:29:39,784
Stay with me.

542
00:29:39,966 --> 00:29:40,966
Please.

543
00:29:41,630 --> 00:29:43,452
I need company right now.

544
00:29:46,280 --> 00:29:49,298
You promised to pick up
my dead body, remember?

545
00:29:49,316 --> 00:29:52,541
I'm stressed as hell.

546
00:29:52,578 --> 00:29:53,636
Fine.

547
00:29:55,320 --> 00:29:56,670
He just needs a man.

548
00:29:58,880 --> 00:29:59,880
It's okay.

549
00:30:20,670 --> 00:30:21,670
KANIT

550
00:30:35,410 --> 00:30:37,121
This is it.

551
00:30:37,164 --> 00:30:39,570
This is the flavor of life!

552
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:42,881
This is pricey,

553
00:30:42,912 --> 00:30:44,549
but we're just going to drink it today

554
00:30:44,870 --> 00:30:46,955
because if not now, then when?

555
00:30:46,973 --> 00:30:48,570
You know how life is, Por.

556
00:30:48,598 --> 00:30:49,140
Mm.

557
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:53,712
You don't know when you'll die.

558
00:30:53,755 --> 00:30:54,426
Right?

559
00:30:54,444 --> 00:30:55,490
Je, I'm here.

560
00:30:56,220 --> 00:30:59,090
So whatever you want to do,

561
00:30:59,152 --> 00:31:01,029
do it today.

562
00:31:01,041 --> 00:31:01,558
I'm leaving.

563
00:31:01,583 --> 00:31:03,029
Hold on.

564
00:31:03,060 --> 00:31:04,333
Stay with me.

565
00:31:04,352 --> 00:31:05,429
Careful.

566
00:31:05,453 --> 00:31:06,875
Je!

567
00:31:06,900 --> 00:31:08,242
My boyfriend is going to scold me!

568
00:31:08,266 --> 00:31:10,863
Stay with me.

569
00:31:12,590 --> 00:31:13,903
I'm going to pee.

570
00:31:13,933 --> 00:31:16,020
When I come back, I'd better see you here.

571
00:31:17,110 --> 00:31:18,998
Or you'll be in trouble.

572
00:31:22,820 --> 00:31:23,820
Je, are you okay?

573
00:31:24,400 --> 00:31:25,400
Yeah!

574
00:31:29,630 --> 00:31:30,266
Hey, To.

575
00:31:30,580 --> 00:31:33,718
Feel free to leave. I'll stay with Je.

576
00:31:35,170 --> 00:31:37,398
It's okay. I can stay.

577
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:39,595
Are you working a lot these days?

578
00:31:39,620 --> 00:31:41,127
Why do you look so exhausted?

579
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:46,666
Why is trying to do something
for the person you love

580
00:31:47,860 --> 00:31:49,380
so exhausting?

581
00:31:52,830 --> 00:31:54,143
I'm so damn exhausted.

582
00:31:59,620 --> 00:32:01,829
Why won't they accept me for who I am?

583
00:32:03,730 --> 00:32:05,878
Is a rescuer like me not good enough?

584
00:32:08,370 --> 00:32:09,693
What more do I have to do?

585
00:32:12,010 --> 00:32:13,675
I don't get to sleep.

586
00:32:13,700 --> 00:32:15,312
I don't even get to spend time with him.

587
00:32:16,990 --> 00:32:18,746
Is what I've been doing really worth it?

588
00:32:19,980 --> 00:32:21,860
If you're exhausted,
why don't you take a break?

589
00:32:23,660 --> 00:32:24,764
I can't take a break.

590
00:32:25,010 --> 00:32:27,140
If I did, how would his father
ever accept me?

591
00:32:29,710 --> 00:32:31,570
I need to keep going.

592
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:42,960
To,

593
00:32:43,550 --> 00:32:44,550
I'm rooting for you.

594
00:32:45,140 --> 00:32:46,746
I know you're a good guy,

595
00:32:49,190 --> 00:32:50,432
but I just want to say this.

596
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:54,580
If you have to try this hard for love,
does it really make sense?

597
00:33:24,790 --> 00:33:25,790
Toto.

598
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:27,000
Oh.

599
00:33:27,610 --> 00:33:28,635
Hi, Kanit.

600
00:33:29,700 --> 00:33:30,820
Did you come to pick him up?

601
00:33:31,220 --> 00:33:34,752
Yes. I'm his boyfriend.
Of course, I came to pick him up.

602
00:33:35,730 --> 00:33:38,549
Well, something's up
with Je Zo. He's sad.

603
00:33:38,573 --> 00:33:39,573
I know.

604
00:33:43,180 --> 00:33:45,109
To got drunk and passed out.

605
00:33:45,630 --> 00:33:47,103
I'm going to get him a cold towel.

606
00:33:58,481 --> 00:33:59,100
Toto.

607
00:33:59,232 --> 00:34:00,232
Hmm?

608
00:34:00,700 --> 00:34:01,164
Toto.

609
00:34:01,189 --> 00:34:02,189
Hmm?

610
00:34:04,900 --> 00:34:05,958
You're here.

611
00:34:07,460 --> 00:34:09,300
Why did you come?

612
00:34:10,710 --> 00:34:11,798
You're really that drunk?

613
00:34:12,530 --> 00:34:13,810
I'm not drunk.

614
00:34:14,950 --> 00:34:16,703
The drinks are just strong.

615
00:34:18,700 --> 00:34:19,983
I'm exhausted.

616
00:34:20,013 --> 00:34:21,533
I needed a drink to take the edge off.

617
00:34:25,350 --> 00:34:26,918
Is it that exhausting to be with me?

618
00:34:28,813 --> 00:34:33,687
You know what? I have to work 24/7.

619
00:34:34,550 --> 00:34:36,075
I do everything.

620
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:39,903
"Everything Toto" can do to make money.

621
00:34:41,540 --> 00:34:42,653
For someone like me,

622
00:34:43,890 --> 00:34:45,650
if I don't do it, I starve.

623
00:34:47,110 --> 00:34:48,110
But it's fine.

624
00:34:49,120 --> 00:34:50,120
I'll do it.

625
00:34:50,510 --> 00:34:51,564
I'll fight.

626
00:34:52,160 --> 00:34:53,312
I'll fight for you.

627
00:34:54,570 --> 00:34:55,663
Don't you worry.

628
00:34:56,390 --> 00:34:58,420
Tell your dad not to worry.

629
00:34:58,450 --> 00:34:59,558
I can do it.

630
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:01,884
Tell your dad to just wait.

631
00:35:01,933 --> 00:35:06,303
Okay? I'll do it.

632
00:35:06,666 --> 00:35:09,152
Hi, Kanit, the math lover.

633
00:35:09,183 --> 00:35:10,635
Hi.

634
00:35:10,672 --> 00:35:12,986
I went to pee, but poop came out too.

635
00:35:13,016 --> 00:35:14,056
That's why I took so long.

636
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:19,226
Is he down?

637
00:35:19,250 --> 00:35:20,807
He must be exhausted.

638
00:35:20,844 --> 00:35:22,800
He's usually a heavy drinker.

639
00:35:22,844 --> 00:35:26,106
He's been working non-stop this week.

640
00:35:26,149 --> 00:35:29,478
Look, he's totally knocked out.

641
00:35:30,180 --> 00:35:30,666
Hey, To.

642
00:35:30,703 --> 00:35:31,703
Clean yourself up.

643
00:35:33,626 --> 00:35:35,390
Or do you want to do it, Kanit?

644
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:37,958
No!

645
00:35:37,989 --> 00:35:38,989
Let's drink.

646
00:35:39,740 --> 00:35:41,023
Bottoms up, or we're not leaving.

647
00:35:41,047 --> 00:35:41,527
Come on!

648
00:35:41,950 --> 00:35:42,950
Cheers!

649
00:35:45,420 --> 00:35:46,432
Would you like a glass?

650
00:35:48,350 --> 00:35:51,220
I think he wants to keep having fun.

651
00:35:52,540 --> 00:35:55,232
I'm going to let him have his fun.

652
00:35:56,400 --> 00:35:57,736
Please excuse me.

653
00:36:04,290 --> 00:36:05,533
Where are you going?

654
00:36:12,709 --> 00:36:16,727
SUVARNABHUMI AIRPORT

655
00:36:17,484 --> 00:36:19,480
He seems so tired when he's with me.

656
00:36:19,660 --> 00:36:22,844
When he was single,
he seemed to enjoy life more.

657
00:36:24,460 --> 00:36:29,207
I think I'm going to ask for some space.

658
00:36:30,160 --> 00:36:31,160
Stop!

659
00:36:31,940 --> 00:36:33,103
Don't be paranoid yet.

660
00:36:33,127 --> 00:36:34,241
You just started dating.

661
00:36:34,266 --> 00:36:35,730
Exactly.

662
00:36:35,767 --> 00:36:38,007
Maybe it'll hurt less
to end it sooner rather than later.

663
00:36:38,200 --> 00:36:39,200
Listen.

664
00:36:39,460 --> 00:36:41,380
Slow down. Calm down.

665
00:36:41,404 --> 00:36:44,149
Problems can be solved.

666
00:36:44,186 --> 00:36:45,367
You can adjust.

667
00:36:45,410 --> 00:36:50,069
You're not the first couple
to live like night and day.

668
00:36:53,340 --> 00:36:55,207
But love shouldn't be
exhausting, should it?

669
00:36:58,475 --> 00:37:00,032
Let me think it over.

670
00:37:01,810 --> 00:37:03,066
Think what over? Kanit!

671
00:37:28,700 --> 00:37:29,789
Damn!

672
00:37:30,626 --> 00:37:32,084
It's 10 already?

673
00:37:32,121 --> 00:37:33,801
I have to drop him off at the airport.

674
00:37:34,740 --> 00:37:36,078
Oh, shit.

675
00:37:37,470 --> 00:37:38,470
Ugh!

676
00:37:44,590 --> 00:37:46,164
Damn it!

677
00:37:46,207 --> 00:37:47,389
He's definitely sulking.

678
00:38:05,229 --> 00:38:05,598
Hey.

679
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:07,120
Kanit!

680
00:38:09,340 --> 00:38:10,767
Why didn't you pick up the phone?

681
00:38:11,780 --> 00:38:12,780
Are you sulking?

682
00:38:14,970 --> 00:38:17,069
I'm sorry
I didn't come home to you last night.

683
00:38:18,470 --> 00:38:20,650
Je Zo made me keep him company
all night.

684
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:22,693
I had to stay.

685
00:38:22,718 --> 00:38:23,856
He held me back.

686
00:38:23,881 --> 00:38:24,881
You exhausted?

687
00:38:25,070 --> 00:38:26,070
Of course.

688
00:38:26,232 --> 00:38:27,734
I wanted to leave, but he wouldn't let me.

689
00:38:27,758 --> 00:38:29,235
I mean being with me.

690
00:38:30,520 --> 00:38:31,641
Is it very exhausting?

691
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:40,343
Since we started dating,

692
00:38:41,300 --> 00:38:43,069
we've had no time for each other.

693
00:38:43,870 --> 00:38:45,973
You've been working the whole month.

694
00:38:47,830 --> 00:38:50,570
I've been trying to find days
off from flying to see you,

695
00:38:50,964 --> 00:38:53,110
but you always have somewhere else to go.

696
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:54,872
It's really for work.

697
00:38:57,270 --> 00:38:59,050
I just want your dad to accept me.

698
00:39:00,010 --> 00:39:01,512
I gave him a promise.

699
00:39:01,561 --> 00:39:04,084
I told you I don't care
about anything else anymore.

700
00:39:05,940 --> 00:39:07,580
I only care about us.

701
00:39:10,410 --> 00:39:13,561
Look, I'm working on a start-up.

702
00:39:14,420 --> 00:39:15,450
I started everything.

703
00:39:15,475 --> 00:39:17,629
I named my page Everything Toto.

704
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:19,370
It's going...

705
00:39:19,407 --> 00:39:20,460
Do you want to stop?

706
00:39:22,693 --> 00:39:23,795
Have you seen yourself?

707
00:39:24,740 --> 00:39:25,943
Look at those dark circles.

708
00:39:26,930 --> 00:39:28,700
You've gotten thinner by the day.

709
00:39:30,070 --> 00:39:31,727
Do you even eat three meals a day?

710
00:39:32,260 --> 00:39:33,300
Do you get enough protein?

711
00:39:33,700 --> 00:39:35,380
Have you even been
taking care of yourself?

712
00:39:38,830 --> 00:39:43,087
If loving me means
you stop loving yourself,

713
00:39:44,530 --> 00:39:47,555
I think we should part ways.

714
00:39:47,604 --> 00:39:49,550
Hey, don't say that.

715
00:39:51,776 --> 00:39:53,770
It'll get better. Please.

716
00:39:54,880 --> 00:39:56,343
I can get back to working out.

717
00:39:56,392 --> 00:39:58,792
It'll only take a couple of days at the gym
to bulk up again.

718
00:39:59,810 --> 00:40:01,346
Or we can go for a morning run.

719
00:40:01,364 --> 00:40:02,158
How about that?

720
00:40:02,170 --> 00:40:04,201
I can wake up at 5 a.m.
and we'll run together.

721
00:40:04,226 --> 00:40:05,226
Please.

722
00:40:06,580 --> 00:40:10,736
Let's just go our separate ways
and live our own lives.

723
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:11,543
No.

724
00:40:11,570 --> 00:40:14,324
So we don't have to carry
the weight of each other's expectations.

725
00:40:18,170 --> 00:40:20,749
Our timing might not be that great,

726
00:40:25,140 --> 00:40:26,693
but thank you for everything.

727
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:31,081
I hope

728
00:40:32,976 --> 00:40:34,970
you find someone
who suits you better than I do.

729
00:40:37,410 --> 00:40:43,721
I hope you find someone
who's less exhausting to be with.

730
00:40:47,432 --> 00:40:51,370
And don't forget to eat three meals a day.

731
00:40:52,010 --> 00:40:55,192
Take care of yourself at work.

732
00:40:57,980 --> 00:40:59,980
Don't forget to apply sunscreen
before heading out.

733
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:05,407
I'll send you vitamins.

734
00:41:05,783 --> 00:41:06,783
Come on.

735
00:41:10,780 --> 00:41:12,109
Don't forget to find
happiness for yourself.

736
00:41:12,121 --> 00:41:13,121
Hey.

737
00:41:13,150 --> 00:41:15,081
You're my happiness.

738
00:41:15,690 --> 00:41:16,690
I should go.

739
00:41:17,190 --> 00:41:18,190
- I should go.
- Kanit.

740
00:41:18,310 --> 00:41:19,844
You're my happiness.

741
00:41:20,170 --> 00:41:20,773
Hey!

742
00:41:20,810 --> 00:41:21,810
Kanit!

743
00:41:22,350 --> 00:41:23,350
Hey!

744
00:41:23,810 --> 00:41:24,355
Kanit!

745
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:25,800
Hey!

746
00:41:28,250 --> 00:41:28,964
Hey!

747
00:41:29,270 --> 00:41:30,270
Kanit!

748
00:41:30,650 --> 00:41:31,650
Hey!

749
00:41:32,020 --> 00:41:33,352
Hey! Kanit!

750
00:41:33,370 --> 00:41:34,370
Kanit!

751
00:41:34,515 --> 00:41:35,936
I'm not letting you leave me!

752
00:41:37,001 --> 00:41:38,078
I'll fight!

753
00:41:38,220 --> 00:41:39,220
I'll fight!

754
00:41:40,800 --> 00:41:42,146
I'll fight for us!

755
00:41:49,530 --> 00:41:50,530
What's up?

756
00:41:51,270 --> 00:41:53,070
Why did you want to
meet at a football field?

757
00:41:54,770 --> 00:41:56,770
When you're at a football field,
you play football.

758
00:42:02,060 --> 00:42:03,844
No. My legs hurt.

759
00:42:04,830 --> 00:42:05,830
I don't want to play.

760
00:42:07,106 --> 00:42:08,164
Don't give me excuses.

761
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:11,284
You were running around just fine
at the Spartan Race.

762
00:42:12,170 --> 00:42:13,487
Football and I are over.

763
00:42:14,230 --> 00:42:15,093
Leave the past in the past.

764
00:42:15,112 --> 00:42:16,300
It's never over.

765
00:42:18,060 --> 00:42:20,189
Everything is still in your heart.

766
00:42:21,230 --> 00:42:23,070
It's just waiting for the
right day to come back out.

767
00:42:26,290 --> 00:42:28,072
Why do you believe in me that much?

768
00:42:30,120 --> 00:42:31,869
I don't even believe in myself.

769
00:42:34,980 --> 00:42:37,481
AKKI 8

770
00:42:42,410 --> 00:42:44,318
Akki from Grade 12, Class 2.

771
00:42:44,336 --> 00:42:45,530
The school's football star.

772
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:47,690
I still see him in you.

773
00:42:49,110 --> 00:42:51,678
Sometimes, your dream just changes shape.

774
00:42:52,560 --> 00:42:56,023
From playing for the national team
to coaching students.

775
00:42:57,290 --> 00:42:58,890
That in itself is incredibly fulfilling.

776
00:43:03,610 --> 00:43:04,610
Come on.

777
00:43:07,500 --> 00:43:08,601
I'll be your goalkeeper.

778
00:43:50,350 --> 00:43:51,364
Thank you, Veha,

779
00:43:52,090 --> 00:43:53,333
for coming back into my life.

780
00:43:55,880 --> 00:43:56,880
Well done.

781
00:44:37,860 --> 00:44:38,860
What's wrong?

782
00:44:39,460 --> 00:44:40,644
Why the long yawn?

783
00:44:41,130 --> 00:44:43,561
I'm fine. I'm just tired.

784
00:44:44,020 --> 00:44:45,020
Oh, Por.

785
00:44:45,250 --> 00:44:47,690
I just sent the pic of me
taking the vet to the dog.

786
00:44:48,540 --> 00:44:49,540
Wait.

787
00:44:49,929 --> 00:44:51,542
Taking the dog to the vet, I mean.

788
00:44:52,400 --> 00:44:53,407
I sent it on LINE.

789
00:44:53,420 --> 00:44:54,731
Was that a joke or a slip of the tongue?

790
00:44:54,755 --> 00:44:55,820
A total slip.

791
00:44:56,915 --> 00:44:58,910
My brain is fried. I
haven't gotten any rest.

792
00:44:59,320 --> 00:45:00,823
I haven't eaten since morning.

793
00:45:00,841 --> 00:45:01,924
A special case came up.

794
00:45:01,949 --> 00:45:05,136
I was going to eat, but now it's 11 p.m.
and I haven't had a chance.

795
00:45:05,155 --> 00:45:07,020
I knew you wouldn't have eaten.

796
00:45:07,063 --> 00:45:08,878
So I got you some congee.

797
00:45:11,290 --> 00:45:12,290
Thank you.

798
00:45:14,130 --> 00:45:15,130
This is heaven-sent.

799
00:45:15,330 --> 00:45:15,856
Hold on.

800
00:45:16,310 --> 00:45:17,050
What are you doing?

801
00:45:17,106 --> 00:45:18,436
Why don't you grab a bowl
and eat it properly?

802
00:45:18,460 --> 00:45:20,016
I'm exhausted. I don't have the energy.

803
00:45:20,040 --> 00:45:21,832
Biting the corner and sucking it out
is the fastest way.

804
00:45:21,856 --> 00:45:24,275
It's okay. I'll grab it for you.

805
00:45:26,896 --> 00:45:27,896
Oh, Por.

806
00:45:28,300 --> 00:45:29,300
You're the best.

807
00:45:37,430 --> 00:45:38,158
Let me pour it out for you.

808
00:45:38,176 --> 00:45:38,712
I'll do it.

809
00:45:38,749 --> 00:45:39,749
No, it's fine.

810
00:45:39,930 --> 00:45:41,487
If you're still hungry, let me know.

811
00:45:41,512 --> 00:45:43,272
I'll get you something else
from around here.

812
00:45:44,650 --> 00:45:45,709
How about rolled noodles?

813
00:45:45,740 --> 00:45:46,826
I can get it for you right now.

814
00:45:46,850 --> 00:45:47,850
I'm good.

815
00:45:48,620 --> 00:45:50,170
You don't have to do all this for me.

816
00:45:51,210 --> 00:45:53,210
It's no trouble at all. I'm happy to do it.

817
00:45:53,241 --> 00:45:55,161
I don't want to see you
going through this alone.

818
00:45:58,780 --> 00:46:00,189
I know how you feel about me, Por.

819
00:46:03,520 --> 00:46:04,884
But I'm still in love with Kanit.

820
00:46:08,680 --> 00:46:10,416
He's the reason I push myself this hard.

821
00:46:11,510 --> 00:46:13,013
I want to build a future with him.

822
00:46:18,200 --> 00:46:22,207
Anyone who gets to date you is so lucky.

823
00:46:22,952 --> 00:46:24,950
If you love someone enough,

824
00:46:26,195 --> 00:46:28,190
you're willing to fight to be with them.

825
00:46:31,640 --> 00:46:34,669
I'm sorry for making
you feel uncomfortable.

826
00:46:34,841 --> 00:46:37,696
It's fine. You did nothing wrong.

827
00:46:38,250 --> 00:46:39,684
You're my brother.

828
00:46:41,170 --> 00:46:44,121
I have to thank you
for making my life so much easier.

829
00:47:00,260 --> 00:47:01,696
That was a brother's hug.

830
00:47:05,444 --> 00:47:06,444
I know.

831
00:47:10,320 --> 00:47:14,835
I'm a little heartbroken,
but I'll get over it.

832
00:47:19,400 --> 00:47:20,400
Want some ginger?

833
00:47:23,800 --> 00:47:24,800
Yeah, sure.

834
00:48:03,580 --> 00:48:04,580
Whose number is this?

835
00:48:05,870 --> 00:48:07,456
Is it a scammer?

836
00:48:08,260 --> 00:48:08,976
Hello?

837
00:48:09,013 --> 00:48:10,453
(Don't you recognize my voice?)

838
00:48:12,170 --> 00:48:13,229
No. Who is this?

839
00:48:13,253 --> 00:48:14,096
(Pailin.)

840
00:48:14,133 --> 00:48:15,133
(Kanit's friend.)

841
00:48:16,650 --> 00:48:17,650
Pailin.

842
00:48:18,710 --> 00:48:22,940
Imagine if your aircraft suddenly hits
severe turbulence

843
00:48:22,983 --> 00:48:24,478
and passengers start to panic.

844
00:48:24,509 --> 00:48:25,900
What will you do first?

845
00:48:26,340 --> 00:48:28,029
First, I'll stay calm.

846
00:48:28,460 --> 00:48:30,792
Um, if the cabin crew panics,

847
00:48:30,823 --> 00:48:32,674
passengers will panic more.

848
00:48:32,698 --> 00:48:34,944
And then I would ask everyone

849
00:48:34,970 --> 00:48:36,570
to fasten their seatbelts

850
00:48:36,626 --> 00:48:38,669
and reassure them throughout the cabin.

851
00:48:40,020 --> 00:48:42,970
What if a passenger starts screaming

852
00:48:43,586 --> 00:48:45,580
and refuses to sit down?

853
00:48:46,170 --> 00:48:46,620
Hmm…

854
00:48:46,675 --> 00:48:50,275
I'd approach them calmly and speak clearly.

855
00:48:50,600 --> 00:48:53,364
Sometimes, people just need to feel

856
00:48:53,395 --> 00:48:54,835
someone is in control.

857
00:48:58,520 --> 00:49:01,690
Why do you want to be a flight attendant?

858
00:49:02,690 --> 00:49:08,835
Because I believe a short flight
can still be a good memory for someone.

859
00:49:13,190 --> 00:49:14,336
Thank you, Mr. Kanit.

860
00:49:15,220 --> 00:49:16,681
Thank you.

861
00:49:20,420 --> 00:49:21,586
How did it go?

862
00:49:22,540 --> 00:49:23,783
I don't know.

863
00:49:23,813 --> 00:49:25,297
I did my best to answer the questions.

864
00:49:25,321 --> 00:49:27,413
I saw them writing something down.

865
00:49:27,830 --> 00:49:29,500
Maybe they crossed me off the list.

866
00:49:29,567 --> 00:49:32,016
Come on. You're definitely getting in.

867
00:49:32,023 --> 00:49:35,776
You'll finally get to run away from
your rescuer lover like you want.

868
00:49:36,490 --> 00:49:37,740
I'm not running away from love.

869
00:49:37,776 --> 00:49:39,389
This is my dream.

870
00:49:40,540 --> 00:49:44,060
But if you really get
in, I'll be so lonely.

871
00:49:44,096 --> 00:49:45,986
We'll be in different time zones.

872
00:49:47,230 --> 00:49:48,903
Don't overthink it yet.

873
00:49:48,946 --> 00:49:50,330
Wait until it actually happens.

874
00:49:50,920 --> 00:49:53,678
But if you really get in, that'd be great.

875
00:49:53,696 --> 00:49:56,503
Because I want to quit.

876
00:49:56,540 --> 00:49:58,595
I don't want to be a
flight attendant anymore.

877
00:49:58,632 --> 00:50:00,958
I want to be a pretty influencer.

878
00:50:00,989 --> 00:50:01,930
So pretty, huh?

879
00:50:01,949 --> 00:50:02,878
I want to be a TikTok star.

880
00:50:02,915 --> 00:50:03,703
Right.

881
00:50:03,733 --> 00:50:04,681
Let's go.

882
00:50:04,736 --> 00:50:07,204
I'm giving you a ride home today. Come on.

883
00:50:19,700 --> 00:50:21,518
Hey, Pailin.

884
00:50:21,536 --> 00:50:22,773
Why are you turning here?

885
00:50:22,798 --> 00:50:24,084
My condo is two streets ahead.

886
00:50:24,103 --> 00:50:26,576
This is a shortcut. Don't argue with me.

887
00:50:26,607 --> 00:50:27,607
Keep quiet.

888
00:50:31,010 --> 00:50:32,010
Ah!

889
00:50:32,460 --> 00:50:33,460
Hey.

890
00:50:34,640 --> 00:50:35,506
My car broke down.

891
00:50:35,524 --> 00:50:35,955
What?

892
00:50:36,410 --> 00:50:37,069
Seriously?

893
00:50:37,093 --> 00:50:38,093
Hey.

894
00:50:38,238 --> 00:50:39,709
The gear isn't moving either.

895
00:50:40,700 --> 00:50:42,165
I'm stepping on the gas, but it won't move.

896
00:50:42,189 --> 00:50:42,601
Hey.

897
00:50:42,644 --> 00:50:43,567
Let me try.

898
00:50:43,598 --> 00:50:45,075
No need.

899
00:50:45,106 --> 00:50:47,070
I think I'm going to call a mechanic.

900
00:50:47,450 --> 00:50:48,450
Wait a moment.

901
00:50:50,010 --> 00:50:51,010
Ugh.

902
00:51:04,920 --> 00:51:06,330
Hey! Over there!

903
00:51:06,355 --> 00:51:07,355
There he is!

904
00:51:17,250 --> 00:51:18,872
Everything Toto at your service.

905
00:51:22,400 --> 00:51:24,656
I thought you said you called a mechanic.

906
00:51:24,798 --> 00:51:27,912
Yes. I contacted Everything Toto.

907
00:51:27,936 --> 00:51:29,143
They can help with everything.

908
00:51:32,280 --> 00:51:33,536
Your car won't start?

909
00:51:33,580 --> 00:51:35,456
No, it won't start.

910
00:51:35,481 --> 00:51:37,875
I've tried many times, but it still won't.

911
00:51:38,150 --> 00:51:39,260
Let me check the battery.

912
00:52:02,650 --> 00:52:03,721
Oh, no!

913
00:52:03,758 --> 00:52:04,398
What is it now?

914
00:52:04,429 --> 00:52:05,930
Where did my ring go?

915
00:52:05,980 --> 00:52:07,512
I just saw you wearing it.

916
00:52:07,536 --> 00:52:08,515
Exactly!

917
00:52:08,546 --> 00:52:11,303
I must've dropped it when I was
reaching for stuff in the backseat.

918
00:52:11,320 --> 00:52:13,266
Can you check for me? It's a silver ring.

919
00:52:13,296 --> 00:52:14,404
What? Why don't you go?

920
00:52:14,435 --> 00:52:15,875
I'm keeping an eye on the mechanic.

921
00:52:15,906 --> 00:52:16,906
Or do you want to?

922
00:52:18,460 --> 00:52:19,460
I'll go.

923
00:52:25,750 --> 00:52:27,075
I only found a coin.

924
00:52:28,350 --> 00:52:29,684
There's no ring.

925
00:52:31,130 --> 00:52:32,583
Hey, what are you doing?

926
00:52:33,210 --> 00:52:34,761
What? Pailin!

927
00:52:34,780 --> 00:52:37,389
My ring is here. I didn't lose it.

928
00:52:37,413 --> 00:52:38,090
Open the door!

929
00:52:38,140 --> 00:52:39,992
You two talk it out.

930
00:52:40,010 --> 00:52:42,995
Or you're not getting out.

931
00:52:43,032 --> 00:52:44,072
I'm going to lock the car now.

932
00:52:44,096 --> 00:52:45,096
Gotcha!

933
00:52:45,720 --> 00:52:47,690
Kanit, you really fell for that?

934
00:52:49,690 --> 00:52:50,690
Hey.

935
00:52:50,740 --> 00:52:52,380
You planned this with Pailin, didn't you?

936
00:52:52,790 --> 00:52:54,870
If I didn't do this,
would I even get to talk to you?

937
00:52:55,460 --> 00:52:56,896
I have nothing to say anymore.

938
00:52:57,210 --> 00:52:58,423
I've made my decision.

939
00:52:58,770 --> 00:53:01,900
What? You made a decision
without even considering my feelings.

940
00:53:01,949 --> 00:53:03,340
You're being unreasonable, you know that?

941
00:53:03,364 --> 00:53:05,666
Hey. Why are you snapping at me?

942
00:53:06,120 --> 00:53:07,616
You deserve it.

943
00:53:07,660 --> 00:53:09,426
I said I'd fight for you.

944
00:53:10,170 --> 00:53:11,696
Of course, it's exhausting.

945
00:53:12,030 --> 00:53:14,687
But knowing I'd get to be with you
makes it all worth it.

946
00:53:19,210 --> 00:53:21,032
What do you mean you want me to
date someone on my level?

947
00:53:21,056 --> 00:53:22,244
No, I won't.

948
00:53:22,940 --> 00:53:25,395
I don't like that. I like challenges.

949
00:53:25,426 --> 00:53:27,118
I listen to Big Ass and Sek Loso.

950
00:53:27,136 --> 00:53:28,896
I love going for something
out of my league.

951
00:53:30,470 --> 00:53:32,072
I'm a dog barking at a plane.

952
00:53:32,096 --> 00:53:33,383
I'm a fighter.

953
00:53:36,300 --> 00:53:37,955
What about the guy at your foundation?

954
00:53:39,176 --> 00:53:40,875
He's like a brother to me.

955
00:53:41,800 --> 00:53:43,352
You know I'm charming.

956
00:53:43,376 --> 00:53:44,976
Of course, people hit on me.

957
00:53:47,500 --> 00:53:48,447
Come on.

958
00:53:48,478 --> 00:53:49,493
I already said no.

959
00:53:49,524 --> 00:53:50,841
I told him I'm taken.

960
00:53:54,200 --> 00:53:55,600
So it's all because you're jealous?

961
00:53:57,000 --> 00:53:58,287
I'm only a little jealous.

962
00:53:58,680 --> 00:53:59,685
I'm more worried about you.

963
00:53:59,709 --> 00:54:01,186
Don't worry.

964
00:54:02,312 --> 00:54:04,310
I've decided to step into this battlefield.

965
00:54:04,349 --> 00:54:06,109
I'm going to fight
with everything I've got.

966
00:54:08,600 --> 00:54:10,853
You have to be my finish line.

967
00:54:16,550 --> 00:54:18,096
I've told you everything I feel.

968
00:54:18,360 --> 00:54:19,720
Aren't you going to say something?

969
00:54:25,040 --> 00:54:25,801
Mm.

970
00:54:25,832 --> 00:54:26,832
That's my answer.

971
00:54:28,527 --> 00:54:31,180
Come on. I didn't hear that.

972
00:54:32,860 --> 00:54:34,318
I'm sorry for being childish,

973
00:54:34,830 --> 00:54:36,250
but it was out of love.

974
00:54:44,420 --> 00:54:47,456
♪ With you and me together ♪

975
00:54:47,487 --> 00:54:48,300
Loud and clear now?

976
00:54:48,343 --> 00:54:50,300
♪ Every day, just like this ♪

977
00:54:50,349 --> 00:54:50,964
Come here.

978
00:54:50,995 --> 00:54:52,960
♪ Through both the
good and stormy weather ♪

979
00:54:52,995 --> 00:54:55,136
♪ Love needs no reason for this ♪

980
00:54:55,173 --> 00:54:56,730
Aww!

981
00:54:56,767 --> 00:54:58,226
So cute!
♪ It can't be wrong ♪

982
00:54:58,250 --> 00:54:59,653
They made up!

983
00:54:59,684 --> 00:55:01,321
♪ To not care what people say ♪

984
00:55:01,370 --> 00:55:03,703
Hello, internet!
♪ When it comes to me and you ♪

985
00:55:04,060 --> 00:55:08,656
♪ We are the reason that stays ♪

986
00:55:24,800 --> 00:55:25,800
Ahh!

987
00:55:26,220 --> 00:55:28,136
Why do we have to pound
the curry paste ourselves?

988
00:55:28,160 --> 00:55:29,329
Can't we just buy it from the market?

989
00:55:29,353 --> 00:55:30,098
Come on.

990
00:55:30,116 --> 00:55:33,667
Southern curry paste has to be homemade
to be delicious.

991
00:55:33,692 --> 00:55:35,698
Every house has its own recipe.

992
00:55:35,710 --> 00:55:38,763
All the men in my family are great cooks.

993
00:55:38,800 --> 00:55:40,929
I'm the only one who's bad at it.

994
00:55:41,780 --> 00:55:44,960
But listen, this is the
most important thing.

995
00:55:45,570 --> 00:55:46,955
If you want to win over my dad,

996
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:49,492
you have to be able to cook Southern food.

997
00:55:49,908 --> 00:55:52,274
The food test is a big deal.

998
00:55:52,608 --> 00:55:53,683
You have to pass it.

999
00:55:53,714 --> 00:55:54,754
Okay.

1000
00:55:54,791 --> 00:55:55,474
Come on.

1001
00:55:55,523 --> 00:55:57,874
Today, I brought you to meet Su.

1002
00:55:57,935 --> 00:56:00,612
She's the head chef for every local event.

1003
00:56:00,655 --> 00:56:02,944
Weddings, merit-makings, and ordinations.

1004
00:56:02,963 --> 00:56:05,443
So, when we get married,

1005
00:56:05,738 --> 00:56:07,221
we'll do it Southern style, right?

1006
00:56:07,628 --> 00:56:08,853
How do Southern people get married?

1007
00:56:08,877 --> 00:56:11,664
Hey, don't think that far ahead.

1008
00:56:11,689 --> 00:56:14,034
Focus on winning my dad over first.

1009
00:56:14,278 --> 00:56:16,206
Can't I dream?

1010
00:56:16,231 --> 00:56:18,717
It's kind of a village wedding.

1011
00:56:18,748 --> 00:56:19,621
There'll be tents

1012
00:56:19,646 --> 00:56:21,000
and Chinese banquet tables.

1013
00:56:21,031 --> 00:56:22,204
We'll prep a whole pig and a cow.

1014
00:56:22,228 --> 00:56:25,086
The neighbors will come over to help cook.

1015
00:56:25,400 --> 00:56:27,135
There'll be a wedding procession.

1016
00:56:27,508 --> 00:56:28,914
Hmm… what else?

1017
00:56:28,957 --> 00:56:29,935
Just a typical local ceremony, you know?

1018
00:56:29,966 --> 00:56:31,928
Oh, I like that.

1019
00:56:31,954 --> 00:56:33,394
It feels local.

1020
00:56:34,768 --> 00:56:36,608
I've always wanted to be
a Southern son-in-law.

1021
00:56:37,468 --> 00:56:38,468
Let me get pounding.

1022
00:56:39,158 --> 00:56:40,158
Southern son-in-law.

1023
00:56:41,998 --> 00:56:43,398
I'm gonna be a Southern son-in-law!

1024
00:56:45,308 --> 00:56:45,732
Ow!

1025
00:56:46,258 --> 00:56:46,686
Ow!

1026
00:56:47,208 --> 00:56:47,923
Chili got in my eye!

1027
00:56:47,966 --> 00:56:49,332
Stay still. Turn this way.

1028
00:56:49,369 --> 00:56:50,157
Whoa.

1029
00:56:50,194 --> 00:56:50,766
I'm going to wash it off.

1030
00:56:50,803 --> 00:56:52,758
Don't rub your eye.

1031
00:56:52,948 --> 00:56:54,188
Stay still, or it'll get worse.

1032
00:56:55,778 --> 00:56:56,212
Hey.

1033
00:56:56,237 --> 00:56:57,237
Right there.

1034
00:56:59,718 --> 00:57:00,551
Feeling better?

1035
00:57:00,588 --> 00:57:01,123
Hold on.

1036
00:57:01,160 --> 00:57:02,040
It's coming out.

1037
00:57:02,083 --> 00:57:03,400
Well, well, well.

1038
00:57:03,424 --> 00:57:05,148
Look at you two flirting away.

1039
00:57:05,184 --> 00:57:06,514
You barely put any chili in there.

1040
00:57:06,538 --> 00:57:07,727
How is that supposed to be spicy?

1041
00:57:07,751 --> 00:57:08,914
Come on, Su.

1042
00:57:08,948 --> 00:57:11,714
I'm already spicy. A little bit is enough.

1043
00:57:11,738 --> 00:57:14,157
Oh, the spicier, the yummier.

1044
00:57:14,181 --> 00:57:15,597
You know nothing.

1045
00:57:16,858 --> 00:57:18,268
I think it's turned sweet instead.

1046
00:57:21,154 --> 00:57:22,154
This is no joke.

1047
00:57:23,726 --> 00:57:25,446
But I'll fight to be a Southern son-in-law.

1048
00:57:25,838 --> 00:57:27,198
I'll do it even with just one eye.

1049
00:57:33,338 --> 00:57:34,338
Whoa.

1050
00:57:34,568 --> 00:57:35,568
Here we go.

1051
00:57:35,648 --> 00:57:36,768
It's starting to smell good.

1052
00:57:38,951 --> 00:57:41,498
Let's add a little bit of this.

1053
00:57:42,358 --> 00:57:44,132
One spoonful.

1054
00:57:44,738 --> 00:57:45,658
Do we need to add MSG too?

1055
00:57:45,695 --> 00:57:46,686
Of course.

1056
00:57:46,717 --> 00:57:47,677
Haven't you heard?

1057
00:57:47,695 --> 00:57:50,274
A little more love makes it umami.

1058
00:57:50,968 --> 00:57:52,815
It brings all the flavors together.

1059
00:57:52,858 --> 00:57:54,317
It's my family recipe.

1060
00:57:54,808 --> 00:57:55,578
Okay.

1061
00:57:55,609 --> 00:57:57,960
I'll remember that
and add it to every dish.

1062
00:57:59,118 --> 00:58:02,989
Next, I'm going to make an omelet
and add this too.

1063
00:58:04,748 --> 00:58:07,517
It's delicious to eat them together.

1064
00:58:07,758 --> 00:58:09,455
Together like we are.

1065
00:58:19,848 --> 00:58:20,637
How is it?

1066
00:58:20,674 --> 00:58:21,674
Yummy?

1067
00:58:22,148 --> 00:58:23,234
So yummy.

1068
00:58:24,077 --> 00:58:26,068
It's spicy and I can't stop eating it.

1069
00:58:27,368 --> 00:58:28,618
The feeling is just like

1070
00:58:28,649 --> 00:58:29,646
when I eat you.

1071
00:58:29,671 --> 00:58:31,424
Oh!

1072
00:58:32,938 --> 00:58:34,181
What are you talking about?

1073
00:58:34,918 --> 00:58:35,918
Don't mind him.

1074
00:58:36,848 --> 00:58:41,363
If you want to be a Southern son-in-law,
you have to know this dish.

1075
00:58:41,394 --> 00:58:44,538
And if you can follow the recipe
and make it for me,

1076
00:58:45,318 --> 00:58:47,849
I guarantee you'll win over both me

1077
00:58:47,886 --> 00:58:49,135
and my dad.

1078
00:58:50,428 --> 00:58:52,206
Get ready to set up the tents, Su.

1079
00:58:52,498 --> 00:58:55,314
I'm going to throw a feast
for the whole town, just for him.

1080
00:58:55,638 --> 00:58:56,638
You got it.

1081
00:59:08,754 --> 00:59:11,434
(Next Episode) They say running a business
with your partner is a breakup risk.

1082
00:59:11,891 --> 00:59:13,214
Let them talk.

1083
00:59:13,510 --> 00:59:14,403
I don't care.

1084
00:59:14,427 --> 00:59:16,125
I only care about how you feel.

1085
00:59:18,994 --> 00:59:20,380
I have to go to the military draft.

1086
00:59:20,404 --> 00:59:22,795
If I'm unlucky,
I'll be stuck in there for two years.

1087
00:59:23,227 --> 00:59:24,519
Don't worry.

1088
00:59:24,543 --> 00:59:26,518
Life isn't as hopeless as it seems.

1089
00:59:27,464 --> 00:59:28,277
Hey.

1090
00:59:28,320 --> 00:59:31,713
If you move to Dubai,
I'll definitely miss you.

1091
00:59:32,644 --> 00:59:33,512
Who's going to Dubai?

1092
00:59:33,536 --> 00:59:34,570
Kanit.

1093
00:59:34,594 --> 00:59:36,434
He made it onto an airline there.

